- "evolved past their initial form" refers to configurations with a version number greater than 1; 
- "protective shields lowered" means the SRL and SRP bits are both set to 0, indicating that protection mechanisms are inactive;
- "identities" refer to the device and configuration IDs;
- "stories of their guardians" involve who created and modified the configurations and when.

sql:
SELECT config_id, device_id, created_by, created_date, modified_by, modified_date
FROM configuration_status
WHERE version > 1 AND srl = 0 AND srp = 0;

